<TITLE> College girl goes on hunger strike 'for marriage' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Thakurgaon, Mar 27 (bdnews24.com)  A college girl in Thakurgaon has reportedly been on hunger-strike since Friday at the family home of her boyfriend demanding that he marry her. Local authorities said Jimun Nahar, an eleventh grade student of Boda Women's College, went to the house of Shafiul Master, father of the boy Sumon with whom she claimed she had been in a long time relationship. Jimun claimed that Sumon, a student of Dinajpur Government College, had entered a relationship with her but was now refusing to marry, said Abdul Jalil, chairman of Auliapur Union Parishad in Boda Upazila. So she went to his family home, at Bhuli in Thakurgaon Sadar Upazila, and began her vigil, the official said. Jalil also said Sumon's family, in a failed bid to get rid of Jimun, beat her up. "But the girl refused to leave and has continued her hunger-strike till Saturday." "We are trying to reach a settlement," Jalil said. bd
